.TH bcopy 3 2024-05-02 "Linux man-pages (unreleased)"
.SH NAME
bcopy \- copy byte sequence
.SH LIBRARY
Standard C library
.RI ( libc ", " \-lc )
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <strings.h>
.P
.BI "[[deprecated]] void bcopy(const void " src [. n "], void " dest [. n "], \
size_t " n );
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.BR bcopy ()
function copies
.I n
bytes from
.I src
to
.IR dest .
The result is correct, even when both areas overlap.
.SH RETURN VALUE
None.
